ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.86                 Enzyme
NAME        trans,polycis-decaprenyl diphosphate synthase;
            Rv2361c;
            (2Z,6Z,10Z,14Z,18Z,22Z,26Z,30Z,34E)-decaprenyl diphosphate synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     (2Z,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate:isopentenyl-diphosphate farnesylcistransferase (adding 7 isopentenyl units)
REACTION    (2Z,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + 7 isopentenyl diphosphate = 7 diphosphate + trans,octacis-decaprenyl diphosphate [RN:R09244]
ALL_REAC    R09244
SUBSTRATE   (2Z,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C16826];
            isopentenyl diphosphate [CPD:C00129]
PRODUCT     diphosphate [CPD:C00013];
            trans,octacis-decaprenyl diphosphate
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the biosynthesis of decaprenyl phosphate, which plays a central role in the biosynthesis of essential mycobacterial cell wall components, such as the mycolyl-arabinogalactan-peptidoglycan complex and lipoarabinomannan [2].
